<br>
The changes to armor versus weapons and reduced effectiveness of crush are bad.  It will not help the classes in Midgard.  Actually it wont help anyone.  The only advantage to this is to help the assassin and casters- who are already overpowered versus melee characters.  I watch as my compatriots are all eating dirt from mezzing nuking backstabbing classes (viewpoint from the dirt on the hill behind them).  The tanks on both sides are already dead or we are overwhelmed in the latest Alb/Hib Zerg.  <br>
<br>
Rather than nerf crush they should have bolstered thrust/slash weapons.  This would have served to strengthen those classes who like using blades/spears without forcing them to respec to crush.  <br>
<br>
Some more armor resistance to certain spell lines would be better too.  For instance, chain/scale be more resistant to cold, Plate be more resistant to fire/earth etc.  But this is a difficult one to pursue.  As for the respec, I am all for it.  Even though I have lost 2 partial respecs from it.  It is common to hear someone say- I screwed up, put 2 in sword and 3 in hammer, what should I do?  Well, delete or wait for respec.  Thats it.  <br>
<br>
I still think that skalds, while evenly balanced, should get the light tank support that other classes enjoy.  More evade, better shield block etc.  I know that Midgard Galahad is devestated while on other servers Midgard is doing well, but we need some more support to help on the defensive end of things.  I am continually watching my character take massive damage from toons of only slightly higher level.  Ouch.  And I was just being healer guard too.<br>
<br>
On mez heal.  I have heard that this will be a single target spell.  While I think that it will not help Midgard in the least, we have no CC anymore.  So, this should not impact the current situation in the least.   All of our healers and shamans have gone over to PvP or Lancelot/Hib and thats it.  <br>
<br>
 <p>Kilgour PeacefulDeth<br>
<Dark Requiem><br>
42 Level Skald  Galahad</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#d1c2a2><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub36.ezboard.com/uarkadi2002.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Arkadi2002</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Team Skald Participant</span><br>  Posts: 5<br> <font color=#ff0000>(7/25/02 9:09:56 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub36.ezboard.com/fteamskaldfrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=241.topic&index=5>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: My opinion</span><hr size=1> I think we're missing the point. They didn't &quot;nerf crush&quot;.<br>
<br>
Crush was a dominant damage type due to a lack of foresight in their definition of the armor tables. Mathematically it worked out that more armor types were susceptible to crush than any other damage type in the game.<br>
<br>
What it appears they've done is re-work the resistances each armor type has to each damage type so that, for each damage type (crush, slash, thrust, etc), there is a &quot;relatively&quot; equal amount of &quot;ideal&quot; armors.<br>
<br>
So, where Sword used to have a high number of &quot;bad&quot; armor types (armor that got defensive bonuses against it) and Crush had a high number of &quot;ideal&quot; armor types, now, they should both have a similar number of &quot;ideal&quot; armor types.<br>
<br>
What this does is bring up the previously &quot;gimped&quot; damage types (I hate to use that word, but thats what people know) and bring down crush a little so that it has bonuses against a few less armor types.<br>
<br>
So, nothing's been nerfed, things have just been equalized and normalized. I'd say its a good thing for all. Now I won't be insulted for swinging a sword, and people won't be sneered at for being cookie cutter for swinging a hammer. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#efe0c0><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub36.ezboard.com/ugisborne.showPublicProfile?language=EN>gisborne</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Team Skald Contributor</span><br>  Posts: 47<br> <font color=#ff0000>(7/25/02 2:53:10 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub36.ezboard.com/fteamskaldfrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=241.topic&index=6>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: My opinion</span><hr size=1> Except it still doesn't fix things...<br>
<br>
Hibernia for example never needs to face scale armor. This makes crush weapons just as effective as they were before for them, while Midgard and Albions suffer. Also, Midgard only has the choice of two damage types, slash and crush. Thrusting weapons would be great imo but we don't have that option. Now we suffer heavily against one opposing tank armor type no matter what we chose. <br>
<br>
Hibernia benefits most.<br>
Albion is neutral.<br>
Midgard suffers.<br>
 <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#d1c2a2><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub36.ezboard.com/ukjeld.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Kjeld</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Team Skald Contributor</span><br>  Posts: 30<br> <font color=#ff0000>(7/25/02 3:40:10 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub36.ezboard.com/fteamskaldfrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=241.topic&index=7>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Hmmm</span><hr size=1> Actually, I think the change in armor tables is a slight nerf to assassin classe vs tanks (which is good). <br>
<br>
The dreaded thrust/dragonfang infiltrator will still be a killing machine against midgard tanks and healers, but is no longer a killing machine against hibernia tanks and healers. On the opposite, he is now completely hosed against them (scales now has heavy defense against thrust). And thrust fares poorly against non tank armor types too, now a blades specced SB (or NS) can imho destroy a thrust infiltrator. So, the thrust infiltrator is not the uber template anymor. Still over powerful agaisnt us mids, but greatly weakened in other areas, so it is not an obvious choice anymore.<br>
Likewise, thrust nightshades suffer also, slightly.<br>
The fact that slash resistance are doubled for chain armor means we won't have anything to fear anymore from slash infils and nightshades. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#efe0c0><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub36.ezboard.com/upfalcon.showPublicProfile?language=EN>PFalcon</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Team Skald Member</span><br>  Posts: 47<br> <font color=#ff0000>(7/26/02 12:11:07 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub36.ezboard.com/fteamskaldfrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=241.topic&index=8>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://www.dallasbest.net/honourbound/images/pf.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Hmmm</span><hr size=1> Overall this is the patch that will bring me back from my NwN Campaign Building, however I must agree that we are still overlooked in every patch for the last few months.<br>
<br>
I have HOPES that some of this will make DAoC worth playing again, however the biggest problems were not addressed as stated above. You can't fight out melee to melee when everyone is lying in the dirt from 2-4 PBAOE Casters that do more  damage in 3 secs than we can do in an entire fight.<br>
<br>
Also I am really sick of reading patch notes and the Skald class is overlooked again, I scroll thru the melee changes, nothing, scroll thru the spell changes, nothing, scroll thru item changes, nothing. As it was stated above what the hell class are we ? I WISH Mythic would decide our role once and for all, and build our skills accordingly.<br>
<br>
Are Skalds balanced ? Well what is your own personal scale ?  Light-Tank ? Back Up Crowd Control ? Caster ? I find it sad that the Skald class is the LEAST defined class in all realms, even Mythic has no clue as to what our role is &quot;SUPPOSED&quot; to be. &quot;We need to make some changes to light tanks, uhmm no skalds arent light-tanks, we need to adjust casters/mezzers, uhmmm no skalds arent casters/mezzers, you know guys we have to address the issue of __________, well skalds aren't those either.&quot;<br>
<br>
If nothing else PLEASE beat them over the head about BS Items, cause that is EXACTLY what they are BS ! Make them Charisma or Resists or just take it off all together, nothing is more irritating than a bogus buff that does nothing.<br>
<br>
Uhmmm hmm after reading all this maybe I am not ready for DAoC again yet ? <br>
<br>
I am TRULY hopeful that this helps, but honestly I have been so burnt by Mythic, if they said the sky was blue I would immediately run outside to check and see, and then wait for them to change it in the next patch.<br>
<br>
PF <p><p><img border="0" src="http://www.dallasbest.net/honourbound/images/acapella_sig.jpg"</p>
